        <p> {{ page.overview.intro|raw }} take us to Pier 1 in Cebu. We urgently needed ferry tickets for our trip to Bohol on Good Friday. After all, it's Easter and nothing much happens on the Philippines during this time. Some locals had also recommended that we buy tickets at the counter early to ensure we could get a spot on board a ship. After almost 2 hours of driving for just 18km, we arrived at Ocean Jet's ticket office and there was already a substantial queue in front of it. We joined the line, and when it was our turn 45 minutes later, we were informed that we wouldn't get tickets for the 2 PM ferry anymore, but alternatively for 3:20 PM. And for that time, please make it business class! </p>
        <p> After getting the tickets, we ordered another Uber online and had it drop us off at the nearby City Mall. After some browsing around, we ended up in the food corner and had something to eat. Then we went to the supermarket to get drinks, yogurt, and fruit. After that, with a detour past the ice cream stand and the donut bakery, we headed to the exit where another Uber was already waiting for us. The return trip went relatively quickly, and so I spent a quiet afternoon in the resort while Basti went to work. At some point, we heard pretty loud music from outside and got curious. We had already noticed during the day that some gay/lesbian association from all over the world was meeting at the hotel, and apparently, they were now putting on their full program. An absolutely brilliant fire show took place right on the beach, which we watched from the pier. </p>
