    <div class="col-md-12">
        <p> At 9 PM it was over, the pier was closed, and so we headed towards the restaurant. From a distance, we could already see musicians going from table to table... oh dear, we don't want that, how embarrassing. Never mind, we sat down, ordered, and suddenly we were next for the music. The 5-member band stood in front of our table and sang something beautiful. After the first song finished, they asked us what we wanted - "Rock'n'Roll"! They were delighted and were quite amazed that people our age would request something like that. They played the Bill Haley classic "Rock Around the Clock" and did it quite well! It's totally strange to be the center of attention, but the band was great! After eating, we saw the dessert at the neighboring table and were immediately hooked. I went to the dessert display and decided we should share a chocolate mousse cupcake. That was the right decision because it was very delicious! Then it was back to the room, Basti continued working, and I ended up in the realm of dreams because I somehow got terrible headaches in the meantime. </p>
